articles.author: James Mackenzie, Maayan Lubell
articles.description: Israel said on Sunday it was delaying the release of hundreds of Palestinian prisoners it had planned to free the day before until militant group Hamas met its conditions, underscoring the fragility of the Gaza ceasefire accord.
articles.title: Israel says it is postponing release of Palestinian prisoners

articles.author: Crispian Balmer
articles.description: The Vatican said Francis, who was diagnosed with double pneumonia, suffered a breathing crisis and needed blood transfusions.
articles.title: Pope Francis in critical condition after health worsens, Vatican says

articles.author: Sarah Marsh
articles.description: The man arrested after a Spanish tourist was stabbed at Berlin's Holocaust memorial on Friday was a 19-year-old Syrian refugee, Berlin prosecutors said, a day before a national election in which concerns over migration are expected to boost the far-right AfD party.
articles.title: Syrian refugee arrested after Berlin stabbing as Germany prepares to vote

articles.author: Reuters
articles.description: A second meeting between representatives of Russia and the United States is planned for the next two weeks, the RIA state news agency reported on Saturday, citing Russian Deputy Foreign Minister Sergei Ryabkov.
articles.title: Russia, U.S. representatives to meet again within two weeks, senior Russian diplomat says

articles.author: Sarah Marsh
articles.description: The far-right AfD likely will score its best ever result as Europe's ailing economic powerhouse lurches rightwards. The conservative CDU/CSU bloc is set to win, but will be unlikely to secure a majority.
articles.title: Gloomy Germans vote in election which conservatives are set to win

articles.author: Michel Rose, William James, John Irish
articles.description: They are expected to argue against a rush to a ceasefire deal with Vladimir Putin.
articles.title: Macron, Starmer to meet Trump as Europeans flesh out ideas for Ukraine guarantees

articles.author: Valerie Volcovici
articles.description: Elon Musk, the billionaire head of the Trump administration's Department of Government Efficiency, threatened on Saturday to fire any federal worker who fails to explain what work they have accomplished during the previous week.
articles.title: Musk orders US federal workers to report on work by Monday or get fired

articles.author: Reuters
articles.description: Canadian Prime Minister Justin Trudeau and U.S President Donald Trump spoke on Saturday, discussing the war in Ukraine and efforts to combat the illegal fentanyl trade, Trudeau's office said in a statement.
articles.title: Trudeau, Trump discuss the war in Ukraine, fentanyl

articles.author: Sarah N. Lynch, Valerie Volcovici
articles.description: President Donald Trump will name newly confirmed FBI Director Kash Patel as the acting head of the Bureau of Alcohol, Tobacco, Firearms and Explosives, a person familiar with the matter told Reuters on Saturday.
articles.title: Trump to name FBI chief Patel as acting ATF director, source says

articles.author: Reuters
articles.description: In a ruined Soviet-era apartment block in Pisky, near the east Ukrainian city of Donetsk, huge chunks of roof and walls lie scattered about the floor where Maria Seryogova once played with her baby grandson.
articles.title: Villagers in Russian-controlled Ukraine visit homes destroyed in long conflict
